        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend_Form_Element_File is leaking configurations into form element markup. An example will better illustrate:\r\n\r\nExpected markup: {code:html}... <input type=\"file\" name=\"uploadElement\" id=\"uploadElement\"> ...{code}\r\n\r\nActual markup: {code:html}... <input type=\"file\" name=\"uploadElement\" id=\"uploadElement\" addValidator=\"NotEmpty 1\"> ...{code}\r\n\r\n\r\nTo reproduce the actual markup above:\r\n\r\n- Form file element must be required\r\n- form need to be processed through isValid()\r\n\r\n{code:php}\r\n\r\nclass Bug_Form_FileRequriedComponentMarkupLeak {\r\n    public function init() {\r\n        $this->addElement('file', 'uploadElement', array(\r\n            'label'         => 'Label text',\r\n            'required'      => true\r\n        ));\r\n        \/\/ ...\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n$form = new Bug_Form_FileRequriedComponentMarkupLeak();\r\n\r\nif ($form->isValid($_POST) {\r\n    echo $form; \/\/ e.g. from view script\r\n}\r\n{code}"
